*Symptoms*: UI freezes for a moment after stage operations.

*Steps to reproduce*:
 # Select any edited file in the working directory;
 # Click "Stage selected";
 # The whole application UI freezes for 1 second, then a popup operation progress window appears and instantly disappears and only after that the UI becomes responsive again.

It is not possible to install it since login does not work.

 

Another bug is it is not possible, to attach the image of the error in this jira. And another bug is it is not possible to select the correct version of source tree in the affected versions drop down, the real version is: [2.1.11.0|https://downloads.atlassian.com/software/sourcetree/windows/ga/SourceTreeSetup-2.1.11.0.exe?_ga=2.9398517.1524312539.1504266591-2027133426.1504266591] .

 

But I sign in with the correct password and username but get the error : Log in to continue - Atlassian account this error occurs all the time even hours later.
{panel}

We've encountered a problem. Please try again in a few minutes.
{panel}

Using a remote like //remote-pc/path/kåre give problems when fetching.
{code:java}
git -c diff.mnemonicprefix=false -c core.quotepath=false fetch upstream
"git-upload-pack '//remote-pc/path/kåre'": git-upload-pack '//remote-pc/path/kåre': No such file or directory
fatal: Could not read from remote repository.{code}
a remote folder with "normal" characters works.

Opening the terminal window and do
{code:java}
git -c diff.mnemonicprefix=false -c core.quotepath=false fetch upstream{code}
works as expected.
